All Implemented Interfaces:
LampOperationI, fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.interfaces.VariableDefinitionsAndSharingI, fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.interfaces.VariableInitialisationI, fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.interfaces.AtomicModelI, fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.interfaces.EventsExchangingI, fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.interfaces.ModelI, Serializable
@ModelExternalEvents(imported={SwitchOffLamp.class,SwitchOnLamp.class,IncreaseLamp.class,DecreaseLamp.class}) @ModelExportedVariable(name="currentLampIntensity", type=java.lang.Double.class) public class LampElectricityModel extends fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.AtomicHIOA implements LampOperationI
The class LampElectricityModel defines a MIL model of the electricity consumption of a lamps.

Description

The lamp can be switched on and off, and when switched on, it can be either in a low mode, with lower electricity consumption, or a high mode, with a higher electricity consumption.

The electricity consumption is represented as a variable of type double that has to be exported towards the electric meter MIL model in order to be summed up to get the global electricity consumption of the house.

To model the user actions, four events are defined to be imported and the external transitions upon the reception of these events force the lamp electricity model in the corresponding mode with the corresponding electricity consumption.

  • Imported events: SwitchOffLamp, SwitchOnLamp, IncreaseLamp, DecreaseLamp
  • Exported events: none
  • Imported variables: none
  • Exported variables: name = currentIntensity, type = Double
